(APPLAUSE)

04:31.546 --> 04:32.889
Okay, let's go.

04:34.841 --> 04:36.218
You look great.

04:48.814 --> 04:51.067
Starina won't go on.
She's a-still in her robe.

04:51.233 --> 04:52.234
Damn!

04:52.401 --> 04:54.449
I don't know what happened.

04:54.695 --> 04:58.199
Go upstairs. Try to get her ready.
I'll be right up. Go!

04:58.365 --> 04:59.412
She won't.

04:59.783 --> 05:03.959
<i>Merde!</i> Have Carmen get ready to do
Starina's number, just in case.

05:09.543 --> 05:12.296
Honey, please.
You got to get dressed for me.

05:12.462 --> 05:13.554
No, Agador.

05:13.714 --> 05:18.185
Victoria Page will not dance
the Dance of the Red Shoes tonight.

05:18.343 --> 05:19.344
Or any other night.

05:19.511 --> 05:21.809
How 'bout just your stockings, okay?

05:22.097 --> 05:23.770
Victoria Page is dead.

05:24.725 --> 05:26.523
But watch how nice
I'm gonna put it for you.

05:26.685 --> 05:27.777
You know how she died?

05:27.936 --> 05:30.906
Alone... weeping for her lover.

05:32.357 --> 05:34.485
Darling, have you eaten?
You look haggard.

05:35.193 --> 05:37.787
Please! You gotta help me a little.

05:38.113 --> 05:39.990
- What is this?
- Supplements.

05:40.949 --> 05:43.202
I bought them for Armand, but...

05:44.244 --> 05:45.746
...that's all over now.

05:46.455 --> 05:48.173
Okay.

05:56.673 --> 05:57.674
Albert!

05:57.841 --> 05:59.218
Agh!

06:00.635 --> 06:02.182
Where are you?
Albert, come on!

06:02.345 --> 06:04.473
- Open up, Albert, baby.
- Get out!

06:04.639 --> 06:07.142
- Open it, Albert!
- Go away!

06:07.309 --> 06:09.983
I don't want him to see me.
I'm hideous!

06:16.067 --> 06:17.068
Fuck!

06:17.235 --> 06:20.489
- (ALBERT) I'm calling 911!
- Agador, <i>abre la puerta!</i>

06:20.655 --> 06:22.453
(SCREAMS)

06:22.616 --> 06:25.540
<i>- (ARMAND) Open the door!
- I'm trying, but he's so crazy.</i>

06:25.702 --> 06:26.703
Albert!

06:27.496 --> 06:28.622
(SCREAMS)

06:29.080 --> 06:30.832
(ARMAND)
Are you trying to ruin me?

06:30.999 --> 06:33.218
Don't look at me.
I'm hideous!

06:33.418 --> 06:36.217
Hideous! Fat and hideous!

06:36.379 --> 06:38.256
Agador, I'm in such pain.

06:38.799 --> 06:41.302
I know, honey. It's gonna pass.

06:41.468 --> 06:44.187
No! It will never pass.
I hate my life.

06:44.346 --> 06:47.441
Are you crazy?
It's packed out there!

06:47.599 --> 06:50.398
That's all I am to you...
a meal ticket.

06:50.560 --> 06:52.654
- I can't stand this.
- Forget about my feelings.

06:52.813 --> 06:56.738
Forget about my suffering.
It's just about your show.

06:56.900 --> 06:59.369
Not even our show.
Your show.

06:59.528 --> 07:02.031
I want a palimony agreement, now.

07:02.197 --> 07:05.201
I don't have one on me.
Is tomorrow okay?

07:05.367 --> 07:07.711
- Don't use that tone to me.
- What tone?

07:07.869 --> 07:12.545
That sarcastic tone that implies you
know everything because you're a man,

07:12.707 --> 07:14.254
and I know nothing
because I'm a woman.

07:14.417 --> 07:17.466
- You're not a woman.
- Oh, you bastard!

07:18.964 --> 07:21.092
Everybody, take it easy.

07:21.258 --> 07:23.727
Whatever I am, he made me.

07:23.885 --> 07:27.560
I was adorable once,
young and full of hope.

07:27.722 --> 07:31.022
Now, look at me.
I'm this short,

07:31.184 --> 07:35.155
fat, insecure,
middle-aged thing!

07:35.313 --> 07:36.690
I made you short?

07:36.857 --> 07:38.109
(SCREAMS)

07:39.860 --> 07:41.828
What do I do?
The number is nearly over.

07:41.987 --> 07:43.455
Do I send Carmen on for Starina?

07:44.739 --> 07:47.117
We have no choice. Yes.

07:47.284 --> 07:49.503
Not Carmen!
How dare you?

07:49.661 --> 07:51.584
- (ARMAND) Do it!
- (ALBERT) No! No!

07:51.746 --> 07:52.998
- Cyril, go.
- Please.

07:53.874 --> 07:57.629
I will go on. The people
have come to see Starina.

07:57.794 --> 08:00.422
Starina will not disappoint them,
even in this state.

08:00.589 --> 08:05.390
Put on the mambo number. Have Beatrice
and Dante get the staircase ready.

08:06.177 --> 08:07.850
- My hands are shaking.
- That's okay.

08:08.013 --> 08:10.186
Agador, I need
some Pirin tablets.

08:10.348 --> 08:12.396
- What are you taking?
- Nothing.

08:12.559 --> 08:15.608
Just one, okay?
One before the show,

08:15.770 --> 08:18.649
and one after.
No more, so don't ask.

08:18.815 --> 08:21.568
Thank you, my darling Agador.

08:21.735 --> 08:23.408
(AGADOR) I'm gonna put
this here for you.

08:23.570 --> 08:25.572
(ARMAND) Breathe.
Ignore the bad things.

08:25.739 --> 08:30.245
This room is so crowded. Can I have
a moment to myself to prepare?

08:30.410 --> 08:32.287
(AGADOR) Let's leave her.
Come on.

08:40.294 --> 08:43.219
Why are you giving him drugs?
What the hell are Pirin tablets?

08:43.381 --> 08:46.430
Aspirin, with the "A" and "S"
scraped off.

08:46.593 --> 08:49.267
- What a brilliant idea.
- I know.

08:51.348 --> 08:54.773
I don't believe it!
You're shaving your chest now?

08:54.935 --> 08:57.108
I didn't have time to wax.

08:58.939 --> 09:02.284
Indifference is the most
awful thing in the world.

09:02.901 --> 09:06.997
I've done everything I could
to make myself attractive for you.

09:07.614 --> 09:11.539
I've lost and gained over
a hundred pounds in the last year.

09:12.535 --> 09:17.837
I've yo-yoed from a 16
to a 10 to a 16, and...

09:17.999 --> 09:19.546
...you've never said a word.

09:19.709 --> 09:24.055
Not one hint of encouragement,
not one scrap of validation.

09:25.382 --> 09:28.807
If not for the Pirin tablets,
I couldn't go on.

09:28.969 --> 09:31.688
If you don't finish making up,
I'll kill myself.

09:34.099 --> 09:35.567
You don't love me anymore.

09:35.725 --> 09:37.272
Oh, shit.

09:37.435 --> 09:39.563
- There's a man in your life.
- What?

09:39.729 --> 09:40.730
I sense it.

09:40.897 --> 09:43.946
And I saw a bottle of white wine,

09:44.109 --> 09:46.407
chilling in the refrigerator.

09:47.070 --> 09:48.868
I only drink red.

09:49.030 --> 09:50.327
And so do you.

09:55.245 --> 09:56.462
There's no man.

09:56.621 --> 09:59.966
I'm switching to white
because red has tannins.

10:00.125 --> 10:05.052
Now there are 150 people out there,
half of them Kennedys, waiting for you.

10:05.213 --> 10:08.934
Waiting to applaud you.
To applaud the great Starina.

10:09.092 --> 10:10.810
Tannins?!

10:10.969 --> 10:13.939
- What do you do while I'm on stage?
- Nothing. I lie here.

10:14.097 --> 10:19.149
Where do you go while I'm killing
myself on stage? I know that look.

10:19.310 --> 10:21.813
Go ahead, hit me. Go on.

10:21.980 --> 10:24.779
That's what you want to do.
Do it. Hit me.

10:24.941 --> 10:26.784
Go on, hit me.

10:26.943 --> 10:28.035
(SCREAMS)

10:28.194 --> 10:30.913
<i>♪ La virgen lloraba</i>

10:33.408 --> 10:38.335
<i>♪ La virgen lloraba ♪</i>

10:38.663 --> 10:40.665
(APPLAUSE)

10:56.681 --> 11:00.231
Ladies and gentlemen,
the one, the only,

11:00.393 --> 11:03.317
the incomparable Starina.

11:03.480 --> 11:04.606
(DRUM ROLL)

11:04.773 --> 11:07.276
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

11:42.060 --> 11:46.566
(STARINA) Thank you and
welcome to The Birdcage.

11:46.731 --> 11:51.157
As you see, I've just gotten back
from safari. I picked up a new muff.

11:53.613 --> 11:55.911
Look, it comes with accessories.

11:57.742 --> 12:00.461
Don't look at me like that.
I didn't kill him.

12:00.620 --> 12:02.622
He died and left me everything.

12:05.166 --> 12:08.636
Oh, where are the couple
celebrating their anniversary?

12:10.004 --> 12:11.847
Mon congrats, you sweeties.

12:13.174 --> 12:15.017
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

12:15.176 --> 12:18.100
I may have something
to celebrate myself very soon.

12:18.263 --> 12:21.392
I think I have found the one.

12:23.101 --> 12:24.102
Yes.

12:25.603 --> 12:28.948
You know I hate to brag, but...

12:29.107 --> 12:32.327
<i>♪ I knew this grocery clerk</i>

12:32.485 --> 12:35.830
<i>♪ Unprepossessing</i>

12:35.989 --> 12:38.412
<i>♪ Some think the boy's a jerk...</i>

12:38.575 --> 12:40.248
(LATIN POP)

12:59.053 --> 13:00.100
Excuse me.

13:02.015 --> 13:03.892
Hello.
What do you think?

13:04.893 --> 13:07.396
You look like Lucy's stunt double.

13:07.562 --> 13:09.906
I'm a combination of Lucy and Ricky.

13:10.064 --> 13:13.443
And it's terrifying.
Get out the white wine,

13:13.610 --> 13:16.830
chill two glasses
and take the night off.

13:17.947 --> 13:20.575
Why you talk to me
like I'm your servant?

13:20.742 --> 13:22.915
Because you're
our faithful houseman.

13:23.077 --> 13:25.956
My father was the
shaman of his tribe,

13:26.122 --> 13:28.500
my mother was the high priestess.

13:28.666 --> 13:30.293
Then why did they
move to New Jersey?

13:30.460 --> 13:34.510
I don't know. They so stupid.
They want me to have a career.

13:34.672 --> 13:39.143
Hello? A career? When you gonna
let me audition for you again?

13:39.552 --> 13:41.270
When you have talent.

13:41.429 --> 13:43.523
Now take off the wig
or I'll tell Albert you wore it.

13:43.723 --> 13:47.899
You do that, I'm gonna tell him you're
seeing someone while he's on stage.

13:49.020 --> 13:51.273
I have two words for you: Green Card.

13:51.731 --> 13:54.484
Now go! And leave
the front door unlocked.

13:54.651 --> 13:57.450
You're such a beast to everybody.

13:58.321 --> 13:59.743
Come on, Gloria.

14:34.482 --> 14:35.529
Hey.

14:44.659 --> 14:46.787
You keep getting better looking.

14:46.953 --> 14:48.751
Thank you. So do you.

14:48.913 --> 14:51.041
Oh, no. Really?

14:52.166 --> 14:54.134
I feel bloated.

14:56.546 --> 14:58.640
- You think I look good?
- You look great.

14:58.798 --> 15:00.220
That's very sweet.

15:02.885 --> 15:05.638
I'm glad you cut your hair.

15:08.016 --> 15:09.609
- Did you eat?
- Yes.

15:09.767 --> 15:10.814
Something to drink?

15:10.977 --> 15:14.902
- Beer, if you have it.
- I do not. Talk about bloat.

15:16.024 --> 15:17.071
White wine.

15:17.650 --> 15:18.697
Swell.

15:19.944 --> 15:22.413
- How long has Albert been on?
- He just went on.

15:24.449 --> 15:26.497
I gave Agador the night off.

15:29.329 --> 15:31.377
So we're all alone.

15:31.539 --> 15:32.791
As requested.

15:34.584 --> 15:36.632
Since when do you like beer?

15:38.713 --> 15:40.715
So, I have something to tell you.

15:40.882 --> 15:44.056
But I don't want you
to get how you get.

15:44.594 --> 15:45.641
Oh, God.

15:47.930 --> 15:49.432
I'm getting married.

15:53.686 --> 15:56.735
I didn't want to tell you
over the phone.

15:57.565 --> 15:59.693
It's a girl.
I met her at school.

15:59.859 --> 16:03.830
It's this wonderful...
Are you upset?

16:03.988 --> 16:05.456
Let me tell you why.

16:06.783 --> 16:08.456
First, you're only 20.

16:08.618 --> 16:10.871
Pop, I know I'm young.

16:11.037 --> 16:16.464
But... you've always said I was
a very level-headed guy. And I am.

16:16.626 --> 16:21.097
I have job offers, I know what I want.
And I have an incredible role model.

16:21.255 --> 16:22.427
- Oh, please.
- It's true.

16:22.590 --> 16:25.309
I'm the only guy in my fraternity
who isn't from a broken home.

16:25.468 --> 16:27.766
Stop flattering me.
It's cheap.

16:32.975 --> 16:34.227
Is it all right, Dad?

16:34.394 --> 16:36.112
Does it matter?

16:36.270 --> 16:38.364
Of course it does.

16:38.523 --> 16:41.743
Say it's okay, before Albert
arrives and starts screaming.

16:42.985 --> 16:44.987
I can't. And I won't.

16:45.154 --> 16:46.747
This is too crazy.

16:46.906 --> 16:50.581
You do this, you're on your own.
Got that, sport?

16:50.743 --> 16:53.622
Don't come back,
don't ask me for anything.

16:53.788 --> 16:55.540
- I want nothing to do with it.
- Okay.

16:55.706 --> 16:57.299
- If that's how you feel.
- I do.

16:57.458 --> 17:00.837
- Fine. Goodbye, Pop.
- Goodbye, son.

17:03.881 --> 17:06.599
- You called my bluff.
- It was good.

17:06.759 --> 17:07.851
- Really?
- Not bad.

17:08.010 --> 17:09.512
I got backed off on a little bit.

17:09.679 --> 17:11.727
Tell me it's all right.

17:13.641 --> 17:18.317
It's all right. I always dreamed you
would. Just not so soon.

17:19.063 --> 17:21.987
Come on. Drop your bags,
stay a while.

17:26.069 --> 17:28.323
Let's drink a toast
to this catastrophe.

17:28.489 --> 17:29.490
I'm kidding.

17:30.992 --> 17:32.744
It's all right.

17:33.286 --> 17:35.038
What's the young lady's name?

17:35.204 --> 17:36.501
Barbara.

17:36.831 --> 17:38.674
Are you crazy? Forget it.

17:38.833 --> 17:40.756
Married? You're not even 18!

17:40.918 --> 17:43.592
Who is this boy, Barbie?
When did you last see him?

17:43.754 --> 17:48.510
Don't call me Barbie. Today at two.
We've been sleeping together for a year.

17:48.676 --> 17:51.475
Oh, God! Has he been tested?

17:51.637 --> 17:54.265
- Oh, Kevin!
- Yes, and so have I.

17:56.601 --> 17:59.354
This has to wait until after the
election.

17:59.520 --> 18:04.572
Where does the young man come from,
Barbie... ra? Who is his father?

18:05.693 --> 18:10.620
His father is in the arts.
He's on the Council of Cultural Arts.

18:10.781 --> 18:12.374
Did they fund the
Mapplethorpe exhibit?

18:12.533 --> 18:17.164
No! Goodness, no.
He's a cultural attache to Greece.

18:17.330 --> 18:18.832
Really?

18:18.998 --> 18:20.625
What the hell is that?

18:22.210 --> 18:26.716
That's kind of a diplomatic post.
It's a sort of an ambassador.

18:26.881 --> 18:28.883
What does the mother do?

18:29.050 --> 18:30.302
She's a housewife.

18:30.468 --> 18:33.267
That's so refreshing,
isn't it, Kevin?

18:33.429 --> 18:34.931
I can't talk about this now.

18:35.097 --> 18:36.314
(TELEPHONE)

18:37.934 --> 18:39.311
- Hello.
<i>- You all right?</i>

18:39.477 --> 18:42.777
Yes. I just told them.

18:42.939 --> 18:45.192
<i>Me, too. And my father is</i>

18:45.358 --> 18:49.909
very excited. He's raising his glass
to toast us right now.

18:50.071 --> 18:53.075
I'm going to put him on.
Yes. Take it.

18:53.241 --> 18:56.085
- You said his parents were in Greece.
- Dad, get off the phone!

18:56.244 --> 18:57.416
Take it.

18:58.538 --> 18:59.960
<i>Hello, Barbara.</i>

19:00.122 --> 19:01.669
Here's to your future.

19:01.832 --> 19:05.086
Shit! No, dear,
that was not my toast.

19:05.253 --> 19:07.381
I broke my glass. I'm sorry.

19:07.547 --> 19:08.969
<i>That's okay.</i>

19:09.131 --> 19:12.351
It was nice talking to you.
We'll talk again soon.

19:12.510 --> 19:14.262
How dare you eavesdrop?!

19:14.428 --> 19:16.681
- You said his parents were in Greece.
- They are.

19:16.847 --> 19:22.069
You saw this boy at two o'clock today and
now he's in Greece with his parents?

19:22.228 --> 19:23.855
No.

19:25.898 --> 19:26.899
Greece?

19:28.442 --> 19:30.536
They're back for the winter.

19:30.695 --> 19:33.164
They're at their home in South Beach.

19:33.322 --> 19:34.699
Is that like Palm Beach?

19:34.865 --> 19:39.416
It's close. It's about two minutes
from where Jeb Bush lives.

19:39.579 --> 19:42.253
Really?

19:59.515 --> 20:00.562
Ah-ha!

20:00.725 --> 20:02.443
- Wait.
- Who is he?

20:02.602 --> 20:05.025
Who? Where's your little chippie?

20:05.187 --> 20:08.282
Will you stop screaming?
It's Val.

20:09.025 --> 20:10.322
Val?

20:11.319 --> 20:13.868
He's asleep in his room
if you don't believe me.

20:16.616 --> 20:18.118
Why didn't you tell me?

20:18.284 --> 20:19.877
Surprise.

21:01.952 --> 21:04.876
- (WOMAN) Mornin', Albert.
- Good morning!

21:08.876 --> 21:10.093
What beautiful flowers!

21:10.252 --> 21:13.256
- (WOMAN) Morning, Albert.
- Good morning.

21:15.508 --> 21:19.263
We have nice, fresh lobster
this morning, Albert.

21:20.179 --> 21:24.275
No, thank you, Mr. Lopez.
Not today. The piglet is home.

21:25.643 --> 21:27.111
You want the cake delivered?

21:27.269 --> 21:32.025
Yes, please. And remember to write
"To my Piglet, from his Auntie" on it.

21:32.191 --> 21:33.192
You got it.

21:33.359 --> 21:37.455
Thank you, Mr. Boynton.
I want to get back before he wakes up.

21:37.613 --> 21:39.911
I'll just try this sample.

21:40.074 --> 21:41.747
Chocolate schnecken.

21:45.079 --> 21:47.047
A triumph. Well, bye-bye.

21:48.374 --> 21:53.255
Perhaps one more schnecken. Do you
mind? When the schnecken beckons...

21:55.506 --> 21:57.133
- Good morning.
- Not yet.

22:01.262 --> 22:02.730
What is this, sludge?

22:02.888 --> 22:05.767
Yes. I thought it would make
a nice change from coffee.

22:07.101 --> 22:10.321
Why don't you tell me
Val was coming, you bad man?

22:10.479 --> 22:13.107
I would not have been
so sassy to you.

22:13.274 --> 22:15.322
Will you put some clothes on?

22:15.484 --> 22:17.828
Why don't you let me
be in the show?

22:17.987 --> 22:20.661
Are you afraid
of my Guatemalanness?

22:20.823 --> 22:21.824
Your what?

22:21.991 --> 22:24.369
My Guatemalanness.
My natural heat.

22:24.535 --> 22:26.287
You're afraid I'm too primitive

22:26.454 --> 22:30.004
to perform with your
little estrogen Rockettes.

22:30.166 --> 22:32.385
You're right.
I'm afraid of your heat.

22:32.543 --> 22:33.669
(ALBERT) Here I am.

22:33.836 --> 22:36.510
The bag lady.
Good morning, Agador.

22:38.007 --> 22:41.056
Wash those, will you? They're
delivering the rest around noon.

22:41.218 --> 22:42.595
Good morning.

22:43.429 --> 22:44.851
My God, that beard!

22:45.931 --> 22:48.229
- Here you go.
- Thank you, dear.

22:52.062 --> 22:54.281
Turkish coffee.
Delicious.

22:54.440 --> 22:55.487
See?

22:55.900 --> 22:57.652
- Is Val still asleep?
- Mmm-hmm.

22:57.818 --> 23:02.244
He must be exhausted, poor baby.
You should have told me he was coming.

23:02.406 --> 23:06.036
I'm so ashamed of how I acted.
But how could I know?

23:07.036 --> 23:11.667
The truth is, you hate sharing your son
with me. You're always pushing me away.

23:11.832 --> 23:17.430
Oh, will you look at this shin?
It's a rag!

23:17.588 --> 23:21.638
No matter how many shirts I send him,
he only wears this one.

23:21.801 --> 23:24.179
You look awful.
What's wrong?

23:24.345 --> 23:25.688
Val's getting married.

23:25.846 --> 23:28.770
Don't be silly.
I got pork roast for dinner.

23:28.933 --> 23:32.858
I wanted to get fillet mignons,
but they're so expensive.

23:34.021 --> 23:35.648
What do you mean, married?

23:35.815 --> 23:37.317
You know what I mean.

23:38.526 --> 23:41.120
- I don't understand.
- Yes, you do.

23:43.489 --> 23:45.332
To some girl he met at school.

23:45.491 --> 23:48.745
Oh, no! Oh, but...

23:49.745 --> 23:53.215
He's just a baby.
He'll ruin his life!

23:53.374 --> 23:55.968
We've been all
through that, okay?

23:56.126 --> 24:00.848
He's getting married, no matter what
we say. The less said, the better.

24:01.006 --> 24:02.474
Oh, my God.

24:05.386 --> 24:07.263
I woke up feeling so good.

24:08.973 --> 24:11.101
Now, all of a sudden, I feel...

24:11.267 --> 24:13.065
...(WHEEZING) so funny.

24:13.227 --> 24:16.697
Just breathe.
Let it go.

24:16.856 --> 24:18.233
Oh, you've heard.

24:18.399 --> 24:23.451
Oh, Value! Oh, my God,
this ¡s such a shock.

24:23.612 --> 24:26.081
I'm not saying anything.
I promised your father.

24:27.658 --> 24:30.832
But at 20, if you throw yourself
away on some dormitory slut,

24:30.995 --> 24:35.375
you'll be sorry the rest of your life.
There! Enough said. Subject closed.

24:35.541 --> 24:36.588
Hey, hey!

24:37.293 --> 24:40.422
Well, don't just stand there.
Give me a kiss!

24:40.588 --> 24:43.262
Or are you too grown-up
for that now?

24:44.425 --> 24:45.472
Hello, Albie.

24:47.553 --> 24:52.309
Oh, Armand, our baby is going to leave
us. And we won't have any others.

24:52.474 --> 24:54.351
Not without a miracle.

24:55.185 --> 24:59.736
<i>When Senator Keeley and I founded
the Coalition for Moral Order,</i>

24:59.899 --> 25:03.995
<i>it was to express moral,
rather than political, views.</i>

25:04.153 --> 25:06.952
<i>What Senator Jackson
is trying to say is that</i>

25:07.114 --> 25:09.037
<i>morality is political.</i>

25:09.199 --> 25:12.248
<i>Abortion, same-sex marriage...</i>

25:12.411 --> 25:14.084
It's a wonderful show.

25:14.538 --> 25:16.757
The most intelligent one
on television.

25:16.916 --> 25:18.213
<i>Pornography would not exist</i>

25:18.375 --> 25:21.504
<i>if politicians didn't
make laws to protect them.</i>

25:21.670 --> 25:24.890
<i>That's why both houses
are now Republican.</i>

25:27.384 --> 25:28.681
It's the perfect platform.

25:28.844 --> 25:34.146
I'm glad I got on Jackson's bandwagon
instead of Dole. Dole is just too...

25:34.308 --> 25:35.434
Dark.

25:35.601 --> 25:38.150
I was going to say liberal,
but he's dark, too.

25:38.312 --> 25:40.030
I gotta fire this woman.

25:40.189 --> 25:42.908
This young man Barbie
wants to marry...

25:43.067 --> 25:44.990
Miss Porter, page two,

25:45.152 --> 25:48.031
paragraph two,
it's "porno," not "pronto."

25:48.197 --> 25:53.203
I wonder if he's old money.
I mean, a cultural attaché.

25:53.369 --> 25:57.374
Your campaign manager is calling.
He says he's got to talk to you.

25:57.539 --> 25:59.212
Thank you, Bridget.

26:09.635 --> 26:10.852
Hello, Ben.

26:12.471 --> 26:13.939
Ready for what?

26:15.599 --> 26:16.646
What?

26:16.809 --> 26:18.231
What's wrong, Kevin?

26:18.519 --> 26:19.771
Jackson's dead.

26:19.937 --> 26:21.154
Oh, my God.

26:21.313 --> 26:23.611
He died in bed?
Whose bed?

26:24.525 --> 26:26.072
A prostitute?

26:27.111 --> 26:29.455
A minor?
And black?

26:30.531 --> 26:35.002
I don't believe this. I don't
fucking believe this! I'm ruined!

26:35.160 --> 26:40.667
You cannot be held responsible
for Senator Jackson's private life.

26:40.833 --> 26:43.803
I'm the Vice President of the
Coalition for Moral Order.

26:43.961 --> 26:47.841
My co-founder just died in the bed
of an underage black whore!

26:48.007 --> 26:50.430
Wait until the media finds out!

26:50.592 --> 26:51.639
Bridget!

26:52.678 --> 26:54.646
I could really use some candy!

26:54.805 --> 26:56.307
You want one of these?

26:56.473 --> 26:57.645
Oh, this.

26:59.268 --> 27:01.566
(CRYING) My baby.

27:01.729 --> 27:05.484
<i>(ARMAND) ♪ Why does it seem</i>

27:05.649 --> 27:10.029
<i>♪ So real to me?</i>

27:12.489 --> 27:15.083
Albert, you're driving me crazy.

27:15.242 --> 27:17.495
I know, but...

27:20.664 --> 27:23.508
Penmanship award.

27:25.502 --> 27:27.755
There's the bar mitzvah.

27:29.882 --> 27:33.102
(WEEPING)
Time passes so quickly.

27:33.260 --> 27:38.016
<i>Well, he looked kind of funny,
but he was smiling, so I didn't worry.</i>

27:38.182 --> 27:40.276
How do they get them on so quickly?

27:40.434 --> 27:42.562
They pay.

27:42.728 --> 27:44.605
They're not mentioning you much.

27:45.272 --> 27:46.990
It's early.

27:47.149 --> 27:50.824
<i>(TV) Senator Jackson's last
words tonight on Inside Edition.</i>

27:50.986 --> 27:54.160
Can you get a good
shot of the house?

27:54.323 --> 27:57.543
We may not make the live shot.
If we must, I'll do a stand-up.

27:57.701 --> 27:58.998
"He looked kind of funny..."

27:59.161 --> 28:01.914
"...but he was smiling,
so I didn't worry."

28:03.207 --> 28:07.087
Yeah, we got a good spot. I don't know
if he's going to... Excuse me.

28:07.252 --> 28:12.509
Why don't you set up there? Figure
you'll get part of the house and me...

28:13.050 --> 28:14.552
I don't know if he'll come out.

28:18.639 --> 28:20.232
Where's Dad?

28:21.016 --> 28:25.066
He snuck out to meet with his advisers.
They wouldn't come here.

28:25.229 --> 28:27.948
I shouldn't have let him go.
How will he get back in?

28:29.817 --> 28:30.864
Mom?

28:33.487 --> 28:38.163
Mom, I have something to tell
you about Val's parents.

28:38.742 --> 28:40.870
They can't blame us for this.

28:41.078 --> 28:44.457
Eli Jackson was a common redneck.
We never saw him socially.

28:44.623 --> 28:48.719
They can understand that, can't they?
Thank goodness they're not snobs.

28:48.877 --> 28:50.800
- (KNOCKING AT WINDOW)
- Oh!

28:59.888 --> 29:01.640
What are you doing here?

29:01.849 --> 29:04.978
I came through the orchard,
over the barn.

29:05.477 --> 29:07.229
You could have fallen.

29:07.396 --> 29:11.651
I did! I'm a wreck. This thing
is all anyone can talk about.

29:12.776 --> 29:15.825
Kevin?
There may be a solution.

29:15.988 --> 29:18.992
What, death?
It didn't work for Jackson.

29:20.075 --> 29:24.000
What about a wedding?
A big, white wedding.

29:24.163 --> 29:27.212
What wedding?
Who's getting married?

29:27.374 --> 29:28.717
No, no!

29:28.876 --> 29:32.221
Why not?
It would restore your image.

29:32.379 --> 29:38.182
A wedding is hope. And a white wedding
is family and morality and tradition.

29:38.343 --> 29:40.471
And it would be such
a special marriage.

29:41.513 --> 29:46.235
The son of a cultural attaché,
a sort of a diplomat, really,

29:46.393 --> 29:49.613
who doesn't look down on us
because of Senator Jackson,

29:49.771 --> 29:54.572
willingly joining our family. It'd mean
the cover of <i>People, Time and Newsweek.</i>

29:54.735 --> 29:58.160
Love and optimism
versus cynicism and sex!

29:58.322 --> 30:03.123
It would be an affirmation! We could get
the Pope's blessing. It's not hard.

30:03.285 --> 30:08.462
No, he's too controversial.
What about Billy Graham?

30:08.624 --> 30:09.716
No, he's too liberal.

30:09.875 --> 30:11.092
Where's the candy?

30:11.251 --> 30:12.673
You've had enough candy.

30:13.128 --> 30:15.881
This boy... what's his father's name?

30:16.048 --> 30:18.471
Armand... Coleman.

30:18.634 --> 30:22.389
(MRS. KEELEY) I wonder if they're
related to Tish and Bobo Coleman.

30:22.554 --> 30:24.602
- Are they from Boston?
- I don't think so.

30:24.765 --> 30:28.395
I think we should go to South Beach.
We should have dinner...

30:31.104 --> 30:33.698
We'll have dinner with them
and stay with the Bushes.

30:33.857 --> 30:39.409
Mr. and Mrs. Armand Coleman
of Greece and South Beach.

30:39.738 --> 30:41.456
(DIANA)

30:57.256 --> 31:02.558
<i>♪ What is this dream I see?</i>

31:02.719 --> 31:06.599
<i>♪ Why does it seem so real</i>

31:06.765 --> 31:08.813
<i>♪ To me?</i>

31:08.976 --> 31:13.527
<i>♪ What if this dream turns out to be</i>

31:13.689 --> 31:16.909
<i>♪ More than a dream?</i>

31:17.526 --> 31:20.200
Fairy dust, fairy dust, fairy dust.

31:22.823 --> 31:26.578
<i>♪ Come, little dream and play</i>

31:28.203 --> 31:30.171
<i>♪ Don't be afraid</i>

31:30.330 --> 31:33.425
<i>♪ Don't fade away</i>

31:33.583 --> 31:35.961
<i>♪ Quick, little dream</i>

31:36.128 --> 31:38.881
<i>♪ Before you're gone</i>

31:39.047 --> 31:42.347
<i>♪ Let's get it on</i>

31:43.135 --> 31:44.307
<i>♪ You... Oh!</i>

31:44.469 --> 31:46.437
I saw that.

31:46.596 --> 31:49.395
Well, this is impossible.
Either I'm an artist

31:49.558 --> 31:53.233
or I'm just some cheap drag queen
trying to get laughs.

31:53.395 --> 31:54.756
(ARMAND)
Let's just get through it.

31:54.855 --> 31:58.029
(ALBERT) I have to understand
every nuance of a song.

31:58.191 --> 32:02.742
I have to give my all. Everyone else can
just "get through it." He's chewing gum.

32:02.988 --> 32:04.456
Chewing gum helps me think.

32:04.614 --> 32:06.616
Sweetie, you're wasting your gum.

32:06.783 --> 32:09.707
Let's keep going.
And no more talking... from anyone.

32:09.870 --> 32:11.292
- I need to talk to you.
- Sit.

32:11.455 --> 32:14.174
- It's important.
- Quiet. He's rehearsing.

32:14.833 --> 32:17.427
<i>♪ And I the dreamer</i>

32:17.586 --> 32:21.011
<i>♪ Each night anew</i>

32:23.008 --> 32:25.682
<i>♪ Tell me, my dream</i>

32:25.844 --> 32:28.222
<i>♪ Are you a dreamer, too?</i>

32:28.388 --> 32:29.640
What is it?

32:29.806 --> 32:33.902
- Can you come upstairs with me?
- No. Not right now.

32:37.814 --> 32:40.408
Did you see what he just did?
Hello, Vallie, darling.

32:40.567 --> 32:43.992
- What did he do?
- He blew a bubble.

32:44.154 --> 32:46.248
He can't do that while I'm singing!

32:46.406 --> 32:48.249
Celsius, look, this may
be a drag show,

32:48.408 --> 32:52.413
but it still has be a good drag show.
If possible, a great one.

32:52.579 --> 32:53.900
Just because you're
22 and hung...

32:54.039 --> 32:55.256
I'll do this, Albert.

32:55.415 --> 32:57.463
- You're the director.
- Thank you.

32:58.293 --> 33:01.297
This is a complex number,
full of mythic themes.

33:01.463 --> 33:03.932
The woman who is singing
invented you.

33:04.091 --> 33:07.095
You are her fantasy. Suddenly,

33:07.260 --> 33:12.391
you, the fantasy, see her, your
inventor, and she becomes your fantasy.

33:13.809 --> 33:16.608
- I don't get it.
- Try more gum.

33:16.770 --> 33:18.022
- Albert.
- I hear you.

33:18.188 --> 33:19.940
Thank you. I know you do.

33:20.899 --> 33:24.199
(ARMAND) Celsius, let's
start with the premise

33:24.361 --> 33:27.740
that when you see this stunning,
smoldering creature,

33:27.906 --> 33:31.661
she transcends your desire to chew.
She electrifies you!

33:31.827 --> 33:35.377
Something starts in your pelvis
and goes to your heart,

33:35.539 --> 33:38.213
where it becomes heart/pelvis.

33:38.375 --> 33:40.719
- Pop?
- Yes? Coming!

33:40.877 --> 33:42.971
What do I do?
Stand here like an object?

33:43.130 --> 33:45.974
No. You do an eclectic
celebration of the dance!

33:46.133 --> 33:50.730
You do Fosse, Fosse, Fosse! Or Martha
Graham, Martha Graham, Martha Graham!

33:50.887 --> 33:56.018
Or Twyla, Twyla, Twyla! Or Michael
Kidd, Michael Kidd, Michael Kidd!

33:56.184 --> 33:59.484
Or Madonna, Madonna, Madonna!
But you keep it all inside.

34:00.397 --> 34:04.118
Work on that. I'll be right back.
It's looking wonderful.

34:05.152 --> 34:06.513
Barbara's coming with her parents.

34:06.653 --> 34:08.576
- When?
- Tomorrow.

34:08.737 --> 34:10.411
That's plenty of time.

34:10.574 --> 34:13.327
There's more. There's a lot more.

34:17.746 --> 34:18.793
Wine?

34:19.081 --> 34:22.712
No. Let's hear it.
I have to get back to rehearsal.

34:26.715 --> 34:31.186
Dad, Barbara's father is a senator,
a conservative senator.

34:31.344 --> 34:35.099
He's running for re-election.
And she told him...

34:38.059 --> 34:41.313
...you're the cultural attache to
Greece and Albert is a housewife.

34:41.480 --> 34:43.027
What?

34:44.690 --> 34:47.695
She had to. He founded
the Coalition for Moral Order.

34:47.860 --> 34:50.909
I don't care who he is.
I don't want to be someone else.

34:51.072 --> 34:52.619
Do you want me to be?

34:52.782 --> 34:56.536
No, no. Of course not.
And neither does she. But...

34:58.205 --> 34:59.752
Dad, he's Kevin Keeley.

34:59.915 --> 35:01.758
Who's Kevin Keeley?

35:02.667 --> 35:03.964
Do you ever read the newspapers?

35:04.127 --> 35:08.633
Of course. <i>Variety,</i> the Arts and Leisure
section of the <i>Times...</i>

35:08.798 --> 35:11.893
What don't I know?
Are you marrying some Nazi?

35:12.052 --> 35:16.023
No. He's conservative,
like half of America is conservative.

35:16.181 --> 35:18.400
And I'm marrying her, not him.

35:18.558 --> 35:20.936
- I need your help.
- Not for this.

35:21.102 --> 35:25.073
- You've done it before.
- Lied about who I am? Never.

35:25.232 --> 35:27.701
(VAL) When I started Edison Park,
remember what you said?

35:27.859 --> 35:28.951
No.

35:29.110 --> 35:32.990
You said if Miss Donovan asked,
I should say you were a businessman.

35:34.324 --> 35:36.918
You were a baby, and she was
a small-minded idiot.

35:37.077 --> 35:38.704
I didn't want you to get hurt.

35:39.621 --> 35:41.999
It's different now.
You're a man.

35:42.165 --> 35:43.667
I can still get hurt.

35:45.252 --> 35:49.052
It would mean everything to
me if you would help us.

35:49.214 --> 35:51.342
It's just for one night.

35:52.384 --> 35:56.434
This is insane.
What do I do, close the club

35:56.596 --> 36:00.066
so I can pretend to be a cultural
attache, whatever that is?

36:00.225 --> 36:04.401
And what about Albert? How do you make
Albert into a housewife?

36:04.563 --> 36:06.361
Well, you'd have to
send him away.

36:06.523 --> 36:08.651
Are you nuts?
You try sending Albert away.

36:08.817 --> 36:13.573
We'd never get him past the Keeleys.
Dad, we have to rid of a few things.

36:13.738 --> 36:15.615
What things?

36:15.782 --> 36:18.752
Well, that, for example.

36:18.910 --> 36:20.958
Neptune?
That's a classic.

36:22.497 --> 36:23.999
And this.

36:24.165 --> 36:25.963
The Kirby?
That's art!

36:26.126 --> 36:28.299
And how about that?

36:35.343 --> 36:36.560
That better?

36:47.397 --> 36:50.150
Look, it's not just
one or two things, okay?

36:50.317 --> 36:52.570
It's everything.

36:53.486 --> 36:56.330
We're gonna have to tone
this down a little.

36:56.489 --> 36:59.117
Just make it a bit more
like other people's homes.

36:59.284 --> 37:04.711
I see. So we need a total redecoration,
so we can be more like other people.

37:05.415 --> 37:08.339
And you're going to
have to try to,

37:08.501 --> 37:12.096
you know, change your
mannerisms a little.

37:12.255 --> 37:15.850
- What are you saying?
- Just be a little less obvious.

37:16.009 --> 37:17.261
I'm obvious?

37:18.303 --> 37:19.520
Pop...

37:30.315 --> 37:32.864
I just had the walls
sponge-painted, Val.

37:33.026 --> 37:34.619
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

37:35.236 --> 37:39.582
You better come downstairs.
She's trying to take his gum away.

37:41.951 --> 37:43.373
I'll be right down.

37:46.998 --> 37:51.799
Yes, I wear foundation.
Yes, I live with a man.

37:51.961 --> 37:54.339
Yes, I'm a middle-aged fag.

37:54.506 --> 37:58.306
But I know who I am, Val.
It took me 20 years to get here.

37:58.468 --> 38:01.517
I won't let some
idiot senator destroy that.

38:01.680 --> 38:04.775
Fuck the Senator.
I don't give a damn what he thinks.

38:13.233 --> 38:15.313
We're still outside the home
of Senator Kevin Keeley,

38:15.360 --> 38:17.704
co-founder of the Coalition...

38:18.655 --> 38:22.785
(WOMAN) ...waiting for Senator Jackson's
colleague, Senator Kevin Keeley.

38:22.951 --> 38:26.455
At this point, we don't know
if the Senator is at home...

38:26.621 --> 38:30.876
(MAN) Earlier reports placed him
at the home of Senator Robert Dole.

38:32.335 --> 38:34.588
(MAN) We're here at what
they're calling Camp Keeley,

38:34.754 --> 38:37.382
waiting for the Senator to appear.

38:37.549 --> 38:40.803
The Senator was co-founder
of the Coalition for Moral Order

38:40.969 --> 38:42.971
with Senator Eli Jackson.

38:43.138 --> 38:46.312
The Senator has been besieged here,
outside his palatial estate...

38:46.474 --> 38:47.475
(WHISTLES)

38:47.642 --> 38:53.149
...by a virtual army of media, waiting
for his comment on the events of late.

38:59.404 --> 39:01.077
Where you driving him?

39:02.365 --> 39:04.038
South Beach, Florida.

39:08.913 --> 39:12.918
<i>There have been a lot of
tasteless jokes going around</i>

39:13.084 --> 39:15.928
<i>about the death
of Senator Jackson.</i>

39:16.087 --> 39:17.680
<i>And here's another one.</i>

39:17.839 --> 39:19.807
<i>(ANNOUNCER) Join Jay on
The Tonight Show</i>

39:19.966 --> 39:22.719
<i>with guests Yassir Arafat
and Kate Moss.</i>

39:22.886 --> 39:24.388
This is unbearable.

39:35.023 --> 39:37.117
Kevin, no!

39:37.275 --> 39:40.324
I'm going down the ladder.
I can't face the press.

39:40.487 --> 39:43.582
Have the chauffeur
pick me up by the orchard.

39:43.740 --> 39:45.834
No! I don't want
to go out there alone!

39:45.992 --> 39:49.792
Barbara will be with you.
It's not you they're after.

39:51.206 --> 39:52.253
Daddy!

39:52.415 --> 39:55.168
Shush!
I'm going the back way.

